Sentencas: Micro-tubular proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) are developed with thin film BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1O3-delta (BZCYYb) electrolytes supported on Ni-BZCYYb anodes.
Titulo: Micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cells with graded anodes fabricated with a phase inversion method

Sentencas: The substrates, NiO-BZCYYb hollow fibers, are prepared by an immersion induced phase inversion technique.
Titulo: Micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cells with graded anodes fabricated with a phase inversion method

Sentencas: The resulted fibers have a special asymmetrical structure consisting of a sponge-like layer and a finger-like porous layer, which is propitious to serving as the anode supports for micro-tubular SOFCs.
Titulo: Micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cells with graded anodes fabricated with a phase inversion method

Sentencas: The fibers are characterized in terms of porosity, mechanical strength, and electrical conductivity regarding their sintering temperatures.
Titulo: Micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cells with graded anodes fabricated with a phase inversion method

Sentencas: To make a single cell, a dense BZCYYb electrolyte membrane about 20 mu m thick is deposited on the hollow fiber by a suspension-coating process and porous Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3
Titulo: Micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cells with graded anodes fabricated with a phase inversion method

Sentencas: (SSC)-BZCYYb cathode is subsequently fabricated by a slurry coating technique.
Titulo: Micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cells with graded anodes fabricated with a phase inversion method

Sentencas: The micro-tubular proton-conducting SOFC generates a peak density of 254 mW cm(-2) at 650 degrees C when humidified hydrogen is used as the fuel and ambient air as the oxidant.
Titulo: Micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cells with graded anodes fabricated with a phase inversion method
